        <abstract>
            <p>On ACR’s paper on glacial origin of lakes. CD thinks it is correct. Suggests further investigation to corroborate it. His only doubt has to do with areas of great activity.</p>
            <p>On ACR’s view of cause of glacial period: CD did battle with Hooker on same point.</p>
            <p>T. F. Jamieson has smashed CD’s Glen Roy marine theory in splendid style.</p>
        </abstract>
